MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5a3a40b1ee4441518f69c26c62cb3cde, type: 3}
  m_Name: Prologue_Fire_Remembers
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueData
  dialogueId: prologue_the_stolen_fire
  lines:
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Title
    text: Prologue. The Stolen Fire
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: Long ago, in the wide steppe where the grass moved like a green sea, there stood a nomadic settlement.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: White yurts sheltered families from the wind, and at the heart of the settlement burned a sacred communal fire.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: To the nomads, fire was not merely flame. It gave warmth, welcomed guests, guarded the night, and gathered people together.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: Beside the fire, quarrels were settled. Before it, the names of ancestors were remembered. Around it, children heard the old stories.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: The elders taught that sacred fire must never be disturbed by empty words, anger, or disrespect.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: But years passed, and people grew used to its warmth. What had once been a heavenly gift became something ordinary.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: They stopped thanking the fire. They stopped listening to the silence around it.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: And little by little, the flame that had protected them began to witness cruelty.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: Fire was no longer used only for home, bread, and warmth. It was used to frighten others.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: It burned the dry steppe. It threatened neighboring tribes. It became a sign of anger instead of care.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: Then, one night, a wind rose over the steppe unlike any wind the oldest nomads had ever heard.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: The sacred flame leapt from the hearth toward the sky, bright and wild, like a red bird spreading its wings.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: Above the yurts appeared Umay, the heavenly guardian of the sacred fire.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: In the form of a radiant bird, she flew over the settlement and lifted every spark, every ember, every trace of warmth into the darkness.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: When the wind finally fell silent, only cold ash remained in the hearth.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: The steppe was swallowed by night.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: Without the sacred fire, the people were left with fear, cold, and regret.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: But one girl saw where Umay had flown.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: Her name was Aisulu.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: Beyond the distant trees, where the old paths disappeared into shadow, the last light of the sacred fire was still fading.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 0}
    speakerName: Narrator
    text: And so began the tale of the girl who would follow the flame and try to bring warmth back to her people.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
